# Everden Visual Gate (agents must play, not just test)

Unit tests (`npm test`) guard **mechanics**. They do **not** gate **Experience**.

## Before claiming presentation / input / scene work done

1. Run `npm test && npm run typecheck && npm run build`.
2. Launch **everden-visual-scout** (Browser MCP + `docs/systems/VISUAL_QA_AGENTS.md`):
   - Fresh save: `localStorage.removeItem('everden_save_v1')`
   - Capture gates **G1–G5** (screenshots)
   - Score rubric PASS / BORDERLINE / FAIL
3. Run the matching **persona agent** from the routing table (fresh-player, quest-runner, combat-tester, or district-explorer).
4. Append run to `docs/playtests/AGENT_RUNS.md` with verdict.
5. Update `docs/PROGRESS.md` CHECKIN — cite run ID and gate results.

## Hard blocks

- **Any scout FAIL** → do not increase Experience %; do not mark R3/R4/R5 visual gates complete.
- **Nick eye test** (Lilymarket, new district art) → Nick only; agents log "pending Nick."
- **Agent runs ≠ T8** → never increment human playtest count from `AGENT_RUNS.md`.

## Minimum playable proof (BG3 rebuild)

| Gate | Proof |
|------|-------|
| Click move | 3 ground clicks, debug ring, character moves |
| One district | Lilymarket: ≤6 NPCs, one backdrop |
| Click interact | Click Pip → walk → dialogue with portrait |
| Transition | Causeway → district → causeway without console errors |
| Exit UX | Player can find exit without reading source (visible marker or HUD hint) |

## Skill

Read and follow `.cursor/skills/everden-playtest/SKILL.md` when executing gates.
